<h4>
    Ethical considerations for the MSc thesis:
    Software development concepts in the computing curriculum at KS2
</h4>

<table style="width:100%">
    <tr>
        <th>Ethical Issue</th>
        <th>How the issue can be managed</th>        
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Use of a vulnerable group – children – in lesson activities.</td>
        <td>No children will be directly recruited for the research, the research will be delivered in a child’s usual setting and by their usual caregivers, e.g. their class teacher, or perhaps parents.</td>        
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Informed consent</td>
        <td>Explanation given to teachers and parents in an introductory email explaining the nature of the research, it’s purpose, the time it will take, how confidentiality will be ensured and what follow up will be given.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Openness and integrity</td>
        <td>The results will be made available to all participants for review.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Confidentiality</td>
        <td>Identities will not be revealed of any teacher, parent or child participants, they will be referenced by class age and all school names will be anonymised.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Using other’s research</td>
        <td>Strong adherence to transparency and correct referencing to ensure nothing is misattributed or incorrectly implied.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Responsibility for recommendations</td>
        <td>Openness and transparency in all results and how any conclusions are drawn to be sure not to present leading arguments and to allow any interested parties to understand the results and independently evaluate any conclusions.</td>
    </tr>
</table>

